00:09:56.630 --> 00:09:58.780
When you do go to
studsterkel.org,

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:01.160
please know that there are a
few ways that you can engage

00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:05.760
in deeper level than typical
radio archives is that you,

00:10:05.760 --> 00:10:09.510
we've got about 164 programs
currently transcribed

00:10:09.510 --> 00:10:11.160
with more coming down the pike.

00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:13.810
And, while transcription
is wonderful and great,

00:10:13.810 --> 00:10:16.000
what you can also
do is share portions

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.460
of the most meaningful bits
across social media platforms

00:10:20.460 --> 00:10:22.800
such as Facebook and Twitter
that will allow people

00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:25.460
to come right back to that
exact moment that you were just

00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:28.330
so excited about you
had to tell everyone.

00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:31.390
Also, if you are an educator
or know some educators

00:10:31.390 --> 00:10:34.720
that are looking for some
exciting content to use

00:10:34.720 --> 00:10:37.410
to enhance their
current lesson plans,

00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:41.100
we do have a classroom
section of studsterkel.org

00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:46.070
where we currently have three
different curriculum already put

00:10:46.070 --> 00:10:49.710
together, lesson plans, audio,
everything, right there ready

00:10:49.710 --> 00:10:52.590
for you to go or your
fellow educators,

00:10:52.590 --> 00:10:55.040
to go into really
have some fun with.

00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:57.420
There's learning based ones,
and then there's project.

00:10:57.420 --> 00:10:58.720
They're all learning.

