Quite obviously, we speak
of a certain game that kids

00:47:39.220 --> 00:47:41.270
in every small town
everywhere, they,

00:47:41.270 --> 00:47:44.450
he was the culture hero,
the baseball player.

00:47:44.450 --> 00:47:45.940
Of course, Cobb.

00:47:45.940 --> 00:47:49.460
Of course, a man like
Crawford, a man like [inaudible]

00:47:49.460 --> 00:47:52.960
and the very colorful and
eccentric Rube Waddell.

00:47:52.960 --> 00:47:55.030
But, there's a little
difference.

00:47:55.030 --> 00:47:57.830
Even though some of the players
today may be equally as good,

00:47:57.830 --> 00:47:59.800
some of the great
ones like Mays.

00:47:59.800 --> 00:48:01.910
&gt;&gt; Baseball took hold
quickly in this country.

00:48:01.910 --> 00:48:04.340
It was a country that,
it was a sport, I think,

00:48:04.340 --> 00:48:08.730
that was very well suited for
late 19th century America.

00:48:08.730 --> 00:48:10.820
And, it took hold very quickly,

00:48:10.820 --> 00:48:13.760
really just got started
in about 1880, 1890.

00:48:13.760 --> 00:48:19.420
And, by 1910, 1915, the top
notch ball player had a position

00:48:19.420 --> 00:48:22.560
in American society in
the mind of the kid.

00:48:22.560 --> 00:48:23.940
Not in the mind of the grown up.

00:48:23.940 --> 00:48:26.530
In the mind of the kid
that was unequaled.

00:48:26.530 --> 00:48:29.040
Or maybe the heavyweight
champion of the world.

