01:09:05.320 --> 01:09:08.010
And, he actually recorded
an album in the '50s.

01:09:08.010 --> 01:09:09.880
It was like a baseball
game kind of album

01:09:09.880 --> 01:09:12.140
where there are different
outcomes and so on.

01:09:12.140 --> 01:09:13.540
I've been trying to,
we don't have any

01:09:13.540 --> 01:09:15.040
in our collection
that I've ever found.

01:09:15.040 --> 01:09:16.930
I've been trying
to find recordings

01:09:16.930 --> 01:09:19.570
of Buck Canel calling games.

01:09:19.570 --> 01:09:23.710
You know, if anybody's got
them, please come see me.

01:09:23.710 --> 01:09:28.790
Because he was the voice
of baseball in much

01:09:28.790 --> 01:09:31.020
of Latin America
and the Caribbean.

01:09:31.020 --> 01:09:35.330
And, ball players who came up
in the '50s and '60s all talk

01:09:35.330 --> 01:09:39.880
about hearing Buck Canel do
calls in their home countries.

01:09:39.880 --> 01:09:46.380
So, you know, that's one of my,
you know, top ten, you know,

01:09:46.380 --> 01:09:50.460
most elusive items is Buck Canel
and other Spanish broadcasters

01:09:50.460 --> 01:09:52.610
who would really be
great to get that in

01:09:52.610 --> 01:09:54.170
because it's a huge part
of baseball history.

01:09:54.170 --> 01:09:55.470
&gt;&gt; Allison Schein Holmes:

01:09:55.470 --> 01:09:57.750
Gentleman in the green
shirt, got a question?

01:09:57.750 --> 01:09:59.050
Yeah.

01:09:59.050 --> 01:10:01.650
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I just wanted
to mention I believe,

01:10:01.650 --> 01:10:04.170
although [inaudible]
actually was

01:10:04.170 --> 01:10:08.420
with [inaudible] during
the actual writing.

01:10:08.420 --> 01:10:13.780
And, [inaudible] came out about
ten years ago, and you know,

01:10:13.780 --> 01:10:19.040
in it, he talked about how
Fullerton really didn't have the

01:10:19.040 --> 01:10:22.480
power to bring the truth out.

01:10:22.480 --> 01:10:26.450
All he could really do was rail

01:10:26.450 --> 01:10:31.120
against [inaudible] how he
really just had [inaudible]

01:10:31.120 --> 01:10:34.110
gamblers and these sort
of dirty politicians

01:10:34.110 --> 01:10:38.090
and was wondering if, you know,
Studs ever sort of, you know,

01:10:38.090 --> 01:10:43.420
detailed any stories
he had about, you know,

01:10:43.420 --> 01:10:45.740
getting [inaudible]
underworld, seedy underworld.

01:10:45.740 --> 01:10:47.770
&gt;&gt; John Sayles: You know,
he, the when I talked to him

01:10:47.770 --> 01:10:49.960
about his own experience
with them, the guy he talked

01:10:49.960 --> 01:10:55.090
about the most was the guy
