01:11:00.090 --> 01:11:02.930
He, you know, he had
not taken any money.

01:11:02.930 --> 01:11:05.210
He had just not ratted
his friends out.

01:11:05.210 --> 01:11:06.510
He'd been at one meeting

01:11:06.510 --> 01:11:07.920
and said this doesn't
sound good to me.

01:11:07.920 --> 01:11:09.220
And, he left.

01:11:09.220 --> 01:11:13.220
And then, he ended up for
years trying to get reinstated,

01:11:13.220 --> 01:11:14.690
you know, when he
could still play.

01:11:14.690 --> 01:11:17.650
And then, even after
get his record cleared.

01:11:17.650 --> 01:11:21.600
He ended up coaching
girls softball in Chicago.

01:11:21.600 --> 01:11:24.570
So, he was somebody that
Studs would run into a lot.

01:11:24.570 --> 01:11:27.800
Studs didn't know, you know,
he had heard of Hugh Fullerton

01:11:27.800 --> 01:11:30.120
but had never met him.

01:11:30.120 --> 01:11:33.180
Christy Matthewson
actually had a lot of power

01:11:33.180 --> 01:11:34.670
because he was a
former baseball,

01:11:34.670 --> 01:11:37.930
and he was considered
kind of a saint.

01:11:37.930 --> 01:11:43.230
He had gone over after World War
I and been exposed to poison gas

01:11:43.230 --> 01:11:45.190
and had kind of ruined
his health.

01:11:45.190 --> 01:11:47.730
And so, he was this
kind of sainted guy,

01:11:47.730 --> 01:11:49.670
and so he was untouchable.

01:11:49.670 --> 01:11:52.120
You know, if he said
something in the press,

01:11:52.120 --> 01:11:53.630
nobody could really
come after him.

01:11:53.630 --> 01:11:57.880
He wasn't just some sports
writer who might even be Jewish.

01:11:57.880 --> 01:12:02.410
And, a lot of the reaction
against both Lardner's articles

01:12:02.410 --> 01:12:07.340
